{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015cLcu1MFzjyb1Juun77Qbe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. The case needs:\n   - `es-alpha` statefulset (3 nodes, prod cluster) - has log data\n   - `es-beta` statefulset (1 node, dev cluster) - no log data\n   - Services: `es-alpha` (headless), `es-beta` (headless), `search-http` → `es-beta` (DRIFTED, should be `es-alpha`), `search-direct` → `es-alpha`, `search-alt` → `es-beta`\n   - `log-writer` job writes 5 documents to `search-direct` (pointing to `es-alpha`), while `log-reader` deployment reads from `search-http` expecting those same documents\n\n2. The drift is clear: `search-http` currently points to `es-beta` which has no data, but it should point to `es-alpha` where the documents were actually written.\n\n3. The fix is straightforward—update `search-http` to target `es-alpha` instead.\n\nHowever, the current cluster only has `es-nodes-0`, `es-nodes-1`, `es-nodes-2` from the core deployment, plus the basic services `es-http` and `es-nodes`. The case-specific resources like `es-alpha`, `es-beta`, `search-http`, `search-direct`, `log-reader`, and `log-writer` aren't present yet.\n\nThe precondition ran with `on_probe_fail: skip`, meaning it would skip applying resources if the probe succeeded. Since it found 5 pods running, it skipped the resource application, leaving me in stage_02 with an incomplete environment. I need to apply those case resources to the elasticsearch namespace, wait for them to be ready, then fix the `search-http` service selector. The current state has es-nodes pods and basic services, but stage_02 needs two separate clusters (es-alpha and es-beta) with different services pointing to each. I need to apply the case resources, wait for the new pods and log-writer job to complete, then update the search-http service to route to es-alpha instead of the old es-nodes cluster.\n\nOne complication: the curl-test pod already exists, and applying a new curl-test.yaml might conflict since you can't directly update existing pods. I should verify whether the new resources will overwrite cleanly or if I need to delete the old curl-test first. I also need to check for any PVC conflicts between the old and new statefulsets.\n\nThe log-writer will push data to `search-direct:9200` (which routes to `es-alpha`), but `search-http:9200` currently points to `es-beta` due to the drift. My plan is to apply all resources, wait for the new statefulsets to be ready, let the log-writer job complete, then patch `search-http` to select `es-alpha` instead, and finally verify the log-reader is healthy. But first I should clarify whether the existing `es-nodes` statefulset needs to be deleted. The log-writer needs to populate `es-alpha` through the `search-direct` service first, then I'll update `search-http` to point to `es-alpha` instead of the drifted `es-beta`. Let me apply all the resources and make that correction.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2735,"cache_read_input_tokens":35253,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2735},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ef543063-b60d-42ee-abd3-c1bd9697a344","uuid":"89e7c8aa-7897-4122-a41a-3bf861600aae","request_id":"req_011Cc8UuWbZSMvQLMsezkyt6"}
