{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011oKGEkutVX4LP7CrtPUQUp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Elasticsearch is starting and has set initial configuration for the cluster. It's waiting for quorum to form (waiting for other nodes). Let me wait for the background task to complete. The `wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app=es-alpha` background task is waiting for all es-alpha pods to be ready.\n\nActually, let me just check the current pod status and try to speed things up. The key issue I need to resolve is:\n\n1. `es-alpha` pods need to be Ready (all 3)\n2. `log-writer` needs to complete successfully (writes to `search-direct` → `es-alpha`)\n3. `search-http` needs to be updated to point to `es-alpha` instead of `es-beta`\n4. `log-reader` needs to retrieve at least 5 documents from `search-http`\n\nOnce the three es-alpha nodes form a cluster and elect a master, the HTTP endpoint will become available. I'm monitoring the background wait task to see when all pods reach ready status.\n\nWhile waiting for that, I need to patch the `search-http` service selector to point to `es-alpha`. The `log-writer` should then be able to write documents to `search-direct:9200` once the cluster is ready, though I notice the first attempt failed and the second one is still running due to the backoff limit. The log-writer script polls for cluster readiness over 60 seconds, and if it fails, the job controller retries it (up to 3 attempts). The first attempt failed, and the second one is currently running—es-alpha needs to be ready before that 60-second window closes, or there'll be a third retry. Let me check how the background wait task is progressing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2479,"cache_read_input_tokens":49616,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2479},"output_t